 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "title-cell",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 🦥 FAQ Answer System — Unsloth Studio\n",
    "**Model:** `TechAvenger/MyFaqSolver` (Phi-3-mini + LoRA, trained with Unsloth)  \n",
    "**Pipeline:** Text Input → Tokenizer → Model Inference → Answer Output  \n",
    "**Runtime required:** GPU (T4 or better) — use Google Colab or Kaggle\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step1-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📦 Step 1 — Install Dependencies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "install-cell",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install Unsloth (auto-detects CUDA version)\n",
    "import subprocess, sys\n",
    "\n",
    "result = subprocess.run(\n",
    "    [\"pip\", \"install\", \"unsloth[colab-new]\", \"-q\"],\n",
    "    capture_output=True, text=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(result.stdout[-500:] if result.stdout else \"\")\n",
    "print(result.stderr[-300:] if result.stderr else \"\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Also install gradio for the interactive UI at the end\n",
    "subprocess.run([\"pip\", \"install\", \"gradio\", \"-q\"], capture_output=True)\n",
    "print(\"✅ Dependencies installed\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step2-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🔑 Step 2 — HuggingFace Login (optional, model is public)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "hf-login-cell",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "HF_TOKEN = os.environ.get(\"HF_TOKEN\", \"\")   # set as Colab secret or paste here\n",
    "\n",
    "if HF_TOKEN:\n",
    "    from huggingface_hub import login\n",
    "    login(token=HF_TOKEN)\n",
    "    print(\"✅ Logged in to HuggingFace\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"ℹ️  No token — model is public, continuing without login\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step3-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🧠 Step 3 — Load Model with Unsloth (4-bit, fast inference)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "load-model-cell",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from unsloth import FastLanguageModel\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Config ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "MODEL_ID       = \"TechAvenger/MyFaqSolver\"   # your merged model on HF\n",
    "MAX_SEQ_LEN    = 2048\n",
    "MAX_NEW_TOKENS = 256\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Loading model: {MODEL_ID}\")\n",
    "print(f\"GPU available: {torch.cuda.is_available()}\")\n",
    "if torch.cuda.is_available():\n",
    "    print(f\"GPU: {torch.cuda.get_device_name(0)}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# FastLanguageModel loads in 4-bit by default — 2-4x faster than vanilla HF\n",
    "model, tokenizer = FastLanguageModel.from_pretrained(\n",
    "    model_name      = MODEL_ID,\n",
    "    max_seq_length  = MAX_SEQ_LEN,\n",
    "    dtype           = None,           # auto: float16 on GPU, float32 on CPU\n",
    "    load_in_4bit    = True,\n",
    "    token           = HF_TOKEN or None,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Switch to fast inference mode (disables gradient tracking)\n",
    "FastLanguageModel.for_inference(model)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n✅ Model ready for inference!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step4-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🔍 Step 4 — Inspect the Dataset Format\n",
    "Peek at the training data format so we build the correct prompt template."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "dataset-cell",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from datasets import load_dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load the FAQ dataset used for fine-tuning\n",
    "# Adjust dataset name/split if yours is different\n",
    "DATASET_ID = \"nisaar/LLAMA2_Legal_dataset_4000_instructions\"\n",
    "\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    ds = load_dataset(DATASET_ID, split=\"train\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Dataset: {DATASET_ID}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Rows   : {len(ds)}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Columns: {ds.column_names}\")\n",
    "    print(\"\\n── Sample row ──\")\n",
    "    sample = ds[0]\n",
    "    for k, v in sample.items():\n",
    "        preview = str(v)[:300]\n",
    "        print(f\"  {k}: {preview}\")\n",
    "except Exception as e:\n",
    "    print(f\"Could not load dataset automatically: {e}\")\n",
    "    print(\"This is fine — you can still use the inference cells below.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step5-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## ✏️ Step 5 — Prompt Template & Inference Function"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "inference-fn-cell",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def build_prompt(question: str) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Matches the training format used with Unsloth/Phi-3-mini.\n",
    "    The model was fine-tuned with ### Question / ### Answer blocks.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    return (\n",
    "        f\"### Question:\\n{question.strip()}\\n\\n\"\n",
    "        f\"### Answer:\\n\"\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def ask(question: str, temperature: float = 0.0, max_new_tokens: int = MAX_NEW_TOKENS) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Run inference through the fine-tuned FAQ model.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        question      : The FAQ question string.\n",
    "        temperature   : 0.0 = deterministic (best for FAQ), >0 = creative.\n",
    "        max_new_tokens: Max answer length in tokens.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        answer string\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    prompt = build_prompt(question)\n",
    "    inputs = tokenizer(prompt, return_tensors=\"pt\").to(model.device)\n",
    "\n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        output_ids = model.generate(\n",
    "            **inputs,\n",
    "            max_new_tokens = max_new_tokens,\n",
    "            do_sample      = temperature > 0,\n",
    "            temperature    = temperature if temperature > 0 else None,\n",
    "            pad_token_id   = tokenizer.eos_token_id,\n",
    "            eos_token_id   = tokenizer.eos_token_id,\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Decode only the newly generated tokens (strip the prompt)\n",
    "    new_tokens = output_ids[0][inputs[\"input_ids\"].shape[1]:]\n",
    "    answer = tokenizer.decode(new_tokens, skip_special_tokens=True).strip()\n",
    "    return answer\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ Inference function ready\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step6-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🧪 Step 6 — Test Single Question"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "single-test-cell",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "question = \"What is the punishment for theft under IPC?\"   # ← change this\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"❓ Question: {question}\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 60)\n",
    "answer = ask(question)\n",
    "print(f\"💬 Answer:\\n{answer}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step7-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📋 Step 7 — Batch Test on Dataset Samples"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "batch-test-cell",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Manual test questions (used if dataset load failed above) ────────────────\n",
    "manual_questions = [\n",
    "    \"What is the definition of culpable homicide?\",\n",
    "    \"What are the fundamental rights under the Indian Constitution?\",\n",
    "    \"What is the difference between bailable and non-bailable offence?\",\n",
    "    \"What is anticipatory bail?\",\n",
    "    \"What does Section 420 IPC cover?\",\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Use dataset questions if available, else fall back to manual list\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    test_questions = [ds[i][\"instruction\"] for i in range(5)]\n",
    "    source = \"dataset\"\n",
    "except:\n",
    "    test_questions = manual_questions\n",
    "    source = \"manual\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Running batch inference on 5 {source} questions...\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "results = []\n",
    "for i, q in enumerate(test_questions, 1):\n",
    "    print(f\"[{i}/5] {q[:80]}...\")\n",
    "    a = ask(q, max_new_tokens=150)\n",
    "    results.append({\"Question\": q, \"Answer\": a})\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.DataFrame(results)\n",
    "print(\"\\n✅ Done! Results:\")\n",
    "pd.set_option(\"display.max_colwidth\", 120)\n",
    "df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step8-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🎛️ Step 8 — Interactive Gradio Chat UI"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "gradio-ui-cell",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import gradio as gr\n",
    "from packaging import version\n",
    "\n",
    "GR_VERSION = version.parse(gr.__version__)\n",
    "print(f\"Gradio version: {gr.__version__}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "css = \"\"\"\n",
    "@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Sora:wght@300;400;600;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap');\n",
    "body, .gradio-container { font-family: 'Sora', sans-serif !important; background: #080a10 !important; color: #e2e8f0 !important; }\n",
    ".gradio-container { max-width: 820px !important; margin: 0 auto !important; }\n",
    "#header { text-align:center; padding:2rem 1rem 1.5rem; border-bottom:1px solid #16192a; margin-bottom:1.5rem; }\n",
    "#header .badge { display:inline-block; background:#0f1220; border:1px solid #252d4a; border-radius:100px; padding:0.3rem 1rem; font-size:0.72rem; color:#6b82c0; margin-bottom:0.8rem; font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace; letter-spacing:0.05em; }\n",
    "#header h1 { font-size:2rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:-0.04em; color:#fff; margin-bottom:0.3rem; }\n",
    "#header p  { font-size:0.85rem; color:#4b5675; }\n",
    "#chatbox   { background:#0b0d15 !important; border:1px solid #16192a !important; border-radius:16px !important; }\n",
    "#question-input textarea { background:#0f1118 !important; border:1px solid #1e2338 !important; border-radius:12px !important; color:#e2e8f0 !important; font-family:'Sora',sans-serif !important; font-size:0.91rem !important; padding:0.8rem 1rem !important; min-height:44px !important; pointer-events:auto !important; cursor:text !important; user-select:text !important; }\n",
    "#question-input textarea:focus { border-color:#3b5bdb !important; box-shadow:0 0 0 3px rgba(59,91,219,0.12) !important; outline:none !important; }\n",
    "#question-input label span { display:none !important; }\n",
    "#btn-ask   button { background:#3b5bdb !important; border:none !important; border-radius:12px !important; color:#fff !important; font-weight:600 !important; cursor:pointer !important; }\n",
    "#btn-ask   button:hover { background:#2f4ac4 !important; }\n",
    "#btn-clear button { background:#0f1118 !important; border:1px solid #1e2338 !important; border-radius:12px !important; color:#5a6a9a !important; cursor:pointer !important; }\n",
    "#btn-clear button:hover { background:#151a28 !important; color:#8fa0d0 !important; }\n",
    "#footer { text-align:center; color:#252d45; font-size:0.74rem; margin-top:1.5rem; font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace; }\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── History format: use openai-style dicts for gr>=4.0, tuples for older ──\n",
    "USE_MESSAGES = GR_VERSION >= version.parse(\"4.0.0\")\n",
    "\n",
    "def chat(question, history):\n",
    "    if not question.strip():\n",
    "        return history, \"\"\n",
    "    answer = ask(question)\n",
    "    if USE_MESSAGES:\n",
    "        history.append({\"role\": \"user\",      \"content\": question})\n",
    "        history.append({\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": answer})\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        history.append((question, answer))\n",
    "    return history, \"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "def clear_chat():\n",
    "    return [], \"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Build Chatbot with correct kwargs for detected version ───────────────────\n",
    "chatbot_kwargs = dict(elem_id=\"chatbox\", show_label=False, height=440)\n",
    "if USE_MESSAGES:\n",
    "    chatbot_kwargs[\"type\"] = \"messages\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── css goes in Blocks() for gr<5.0, in launch() for gr>=5.0 ─────────────────\n",
    "CSS_IN_BLOCKS = GR_VERSION < version.parse(\"5.0.0\")\n",
    "\n",
    "blocks_kwargs = {\"title\": \"FAQ Agent — Unsloth\"}\n",
    "if CSS_IN_BLOCKS:\n",
    "    blocks_kwargs[\"css\"] = css\n",
    "\n",
    "with gr.Blocks(**blocks_kwargs) as demo:\n",
    "    gr.HTML(\"\"\"\n",
    "    <div id=\\\"header\\\">\n",
    "        <div class=\\\"badge\\\">Phi-3-mini · QLoRA · Unsloth · TechAvenger/MyFaqSolver</div>\n",
    "        <h1>FAQ Answer Agent</h1>\n",
    "        <p>Powered by your Unsloth fine-tuned model — fast 4-bit inference</p>\n",
    "    </div>\"\"\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    chatbot = gr.Chatbot(**chatbot_kwargs)\n",
    "\n",
    "    with gr.Row():\n",
    "        q_input   = gr.Textbox(elem_id=\"question-input\", placeholder=\"Ask your FAQ question here...\",\n",
    "                               lines=1, max_lines=4, show_label=False, scale=8, interactive=True, autofocus=True)\n",
    "        ask_btn   = gr.Button(\"Ask →\",  elem_id=\"btn-ask\",   variant=\"primary\",   scale=1, min_width=80)\n",
    "        clear_btn = gr.Button(\"Clear\",  elem_id=\"btn-clear\", variant=\"secondary\", scale=1, min_width=70)\n",
    "\n",
    "    gr.HTML('<div id=\"footer\">TechAvenger/MyFaqSolver · Phi-3-mini-4k base · LoRA r=16 · Unsloth 4-bit</div>')\n",
    "\n",
    "    ask_btn.click(fn=chat,       inputs=[q_input, chatbot], outputs=[chatbot, q_input])\n",
    "    q_input.submit(fn=chat,      inputs=[q_input, chatbot], outputs=[chatbot, q_input])\n",
    "    clear_btn.click(fn=clear_chat, outputs=[chatbot, q_input])\n",
    "\n",
    "# share=True gives a public URL valid for 72h (useful in Colab)\n",
    "launch_kwargs = {\"share\": True}\n",
    "if not CSS_IN_BLOCKS:\n",
    "    launch_kwargs[\"css\"] = css\n",
    "\n",
    "demo.launch(**launch_kwargs)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step9-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 💾 Step 9 — (Optional) Export Answers to CSV"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "export-cell",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Run your own questions in bulk and save results\n",
    "my_questions = [\n",
    "    # ← Add as many questions as you like\n",
    "    \"What is Section 144 CrPC?\",\n",
    "    \"What is the right to information act?\",\n",
    "    \"What is the limitation period for filing a civil suit?\",\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "rows = []\n",
    "for q in my_questions:\n",
    "    print(f\"Processing: {q[:60]}...\")\n",
    "    rows.append({\"question\": q, \"answer\": ask(q)})\n",
    "\n",
    "out_df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\n",
    "out_df.to_csv(\"faq_results.csv\", index=False)\n",
    "print(\"\\n✅ Saved to faq_results.csv\")\n",
    "out_df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "tips-cell",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 📝 Tips\n",
    "\n",
    "| Topic | Detail |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| **Speed** | Unsloth 4-bit inference is ~2x faster than vanilla HF on same GPU |\n",
    "| **Temperature** | Use `temperature=0.0` (default) for consistent FAQ answers; `0.3–0.7` for more varied responses |\n",
    "| **Max tokens** | `MAX_NEW_TOKENS=256` is good for FAQ; increase to 512 for detailed legal explanations |\n",
    "| **Public URL** | `share=True` in `demo.launch()` gives a 72-hour public Gradio link |\n",
    "| **Model source** | The notebook loads the **merged model** from `TechAvenger/MyFaqSolver` (no separate base + adapter needed) |\n",
    "| **Local run** | On CPU without GPU this will be slow (~2-5 min/answer); always use GPU runtime |\n"
   ]
  }
 ]
}\n
